description: Made in USA  We only know one way to beat your expectations.  Use the best materials, and the best methods.  Like every shoe in the Dexter 1957 Collection, the Pembroke is made using the hand-sewn moccasin method of shoemaking.  This ancient method, demands the use of large quantities of leather and time. We use one large piece of leather wrapped all the way under, and up the side of your foot and then sew this piece by hand to the plug, the piece of leather that covers the top of your foot.  Making shoes this way is hard work.  But the result is a pair of shoes that beat your expectations. description: Made in USA  The Gilford is constructed with full-grain leather, and this is an important distinction.  Of the thousands of hides that pass through a tannery only two in every ten have a grain tight enough to earn the distinction full-grain.  So what does this mean for you? Full-grain means long-life, the cell structure is strong and closely knit. Full-grain means deep, rich color, so youll look sharp when wearing your favorite suit or dress pants.  Full-grain means the ability to withstand harsh weather better than most leathers, so you can wear these shoes all year long.
